[4] Cholera, diarrhea - India (Kerala)
Date: Mon 23 Jun 2014
Source: The Times of India [edited]
http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/City/Kochi/Ernakulam-district-put-on-cholera-alert/articleshow/37067407.cms


With cases of cholera being reported from various parts of the state [Kerala], the Ernakulam health department has issued a warning to contain the spread of the disease in the district. Though no cholera case has been reported from the district in 2014, around 11 035 people were reported to have suffered from diarrhea from January to May in 2014. "We have warned the public to keep vigil," said P N Sreenivasan, rural health officer.

The disease results from eating food or drinking water contaminated with a bacterium called _Vibrio cholerae_. "As cholera is a water and food-borne disease, people should be extra vigilant. They should avoid eating cold food kept in refrigerators. They should also ensure that they eat only fresh and hot food served by hotels and eateries," Sreenivasan said.

