[6] Diarrhea - India (Tamil Nadu)
Date: Fri 13 Jun 2014l
Source: Jagran Post [edited]
http://post.jagran.com/tamil-nadu-two-infants-die-of-diarrhea-six-take-ill-1402645078


Two babies, who were twin brothers, were suffering from severe diarrhea and vomiting and died at their home in Konganapuram Panchayat Union area [Tamil Nadu state], District Revenue Officer Selvaraj said. He said 6 other children under 2 years also had same symptoms and were admitted to the government hospital in Edapadi.

The DRO said on hearing about the death of the children, he deputed Sankari Revenue Officer and Edapadi Thasildhar to ascertain the situation. Joint Director of Health Dr Aadimolam said that the twins died due to dehydration, and the other 6 children were recovering.

The cause of death of the 2 children was being investigated; he said [additional] health teams had been posted in the village.

